{{!< default}}
{{!-- Subscription landing page. Routed via routes.yaml (/subscribe/ → template: subscribe).
      The subscribe partial renders the live members form when membership is enabled. --}}
<header class="hero">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="sys-label">// subscribe</div>
    <h1>Stay in the loop</h1>
    <div class="hero-sub">New writing by email — CTF writeups and repeatable security methodology. No noise.</div>
  </div>
</header>

<div class="container narrow">

  {{> subscribe}}

  <div class="section-break"><h2>What subscribers get</h2></div>
  <div class="pf-strip">
    <div class="pf-item">
      <span class="pf-kind">CTF writeups</span>
      <p>TryHackMe and HackTheBox walkthroughs — enumeration to root, with the methodology made
      explicit and repeatable, not just the commands.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="pf-item">
      <span class="pf-kind">Methodology</span>
      <p>The recon and assessment process behind the tooling: checklists, reasoning, and the
      framework that makes results reproducible.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="pf-item">
      <span class="pf-kind">Security notes</span>
      <p>Security+ study distilled, tool spotlights, and detection-engineering notes from the
      Wazuh SIEM lab build.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <p>No spam, no fixed schedule — only when something worth reading goes up. Unsubscribe any time.
  Prefer the source? Everything traces back to the
  <a href="https://rootdrifter.github.io" rel="noopener">portfolio</a>.</p>

</div>
